d 'GSHEETS': module to import and export Google Sheets data in Stata
d
d  gsheets provides direct integration with Google Sheets via the
d  Google Sheets API v4. It allows Stata users to import data from
d  any Google Sheet directly into Stata, and export Stata datasets
d  back to Google Sheets, without leaving the Stata environment.
d
d  Commands included:
d
d  gs4_auth authenticates with Google using OAuth2 browser flow,
d  service account, or API key. Credentials are cached and refresh
d  automatically across sessions.
d
d  gs4_deauth clears cached Google credentials.
d
d  gs4_get retrieves spreadsheet metadata including title, number
d  of sheets, and sheet names.
d
d  import_gsheet imports data from a Google Sheet into Stata.
d  Supports sheet name, cell range, and firstrow options. Uses
d  parallel HTTP requests for large sheets (over 10,000 rows).
d
d  export_gsheet exports the current Stata dataset to a Google
d  Sheet. Supports if/in subsetting, replace and schema-aware
d  append modes, variable labels as headers, and a generate()
d  option that adds a Stata-formatted datetime audit column.
d  Automatically creates the target sheet tab if it does not exist.
d
d  Requires: Stata 17 or later, Java 11 or later (bundled with
d  Stata 17+), Google Cloud project with Sheets API enabled.
d  OAuth2 or service account required for export_gsheet.
d  API key sufficient for reading public sheets.
d
d  KW: Google Sheets
d  KW: import
d  KW: export
d  KW: API
d  KW: data management
d  KW: web data
d
d  Requires: Stata version 17
d
d  Author: Fahad Mirza
d  Support: email fahad.mirza@example.com
d
d  Distribution-Date: 20260327
d  Version: 1.1.0
d
f gsheets.jar
f gs4_auth.ado
f gs4_deauth.ado
f gs4_get.ado
f import_gsheet.ado
f export_gsheet.ado
f gs4_auth.sthlp
f gs4_deauth.sthlp
f gs4_get.sthlp
f import_gsheet.sthlp
f export_gsheet.sthlp
